  "prompt": "Which is the best brand of whisky in India?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" brand of whisky can be quite subjective, as it depends on personal preferences in flavor, price, and regional availability. However, in India, there are several popular and highly regarded whisky brands:\n\n1. **Amrut**: Known for its single malt offerings, Amrut has garnered international acclaim for its quality and distinct flavors.\n  \n2. **Paul John**: Another Indian single malt brand that has received positive reviews both domestically and internationally.\n\n3. **Rampur**: A luxury single malt brand that is steadily gaining recognition for its premium quality.\n\n4. **Royal Stag**: Popular for its affordability and wide availability, making it a favorite among many Indian whisky drinkers.\n\n5. **McDowell\u2019s No. 1**: One of the best-selling whisky brands in India, appreciated for its budget-friendly options.\n\n6. **Officer\u2019s Choice**: Known for being one of the highest-selling whiskies in the world, it's a popular choice in India.\n\n7. **Blenders Pride**: A premium blend that many whisky enthusiasts appreciate for its smooth taste.\n\nEach of these brands offers a range of products catering to different tastes and budgets. If you're looking for premium quality, Amrut, Paul John, and Rampur are excellent choices. For more budget-friendly options with good quality, Royal Stag, McDowell's No. 1, Officer's Choice, and Blenders Pride are noteworthy. Ultimately, the best whisky brand for you would depend on your personal preference and taste.",
